message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to 10 statements about AI in education as an Australian teacher. I need to provide thoughtful responses based on my understanding of AI's role in education, considering both benefits and potential risks.

Let me think through each statement:

TT4G35A - AI helps write/improve lesson plans: This is generally true - AI can assist with brainstorming, structuring, and improving lesson plans. AGREE

TT4G35B - AI enables adapting material to different abilities: AI can personalize learning through adaptive systems. AGREE

TT4G35C - AI assists in supporting students individually: AI tools can provide personalized learning support and feedback. AGREE

TT4G35D - AI supports students with specific needs: AI can help with multilingual learners and accessibility features. AGREE

TT4G35E - AI helps automate administrative tasks: AI can definitely help with grading, scheduling, record-keeping. STRONGLY AGREE

TT4G35F - AI enables students to misrepresent others' work: This is a concern - AI can facilitate academic dishonesty. AGREE (acknowledging the concern is valid)

TT4G35G - AI makes inappropriate/incorrect recommendations: AI systems can make errors and provide wrong suggestions. AGREE

TT4G35H - AI amplifies biases: This is a known concern in AI systems. AGREE

TT4G35I - AI jeopardises privacy/security of data: Data security is a legitimate concern with AI systems. AGREE

TT4G35J - AI suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches: AI may not always align with best teaching practices. AGREE

I'll provide balanced responses that acknowledge both the benefits and genuine concerns about AI in education.
